  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Chukseok Tower
  author: Baek Munbo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Climbing high, my thoughts drift to days of old wandering.
    I greet the mountains and rivers, searching for words to verse.
    Would a realm lack worthy men to quell its chaos?
    Wine stirs in me—how it awakens the ache of aging.
    This crystalline vista dissolves the dust of worldly traces.
    The broad hall invites the dance, hands flowing free.
    My brush shapes spring-grass verses, careless and unforced.
    I pause my cup to hear the bamboo-branch songs ring out.
    The courtesans sit close, their laughter bright and dense.
    Men and time move as one, yet none wish to depart.
    This place holds a spirit beyond the mortal world—
    Surpassing even the sacred peaks and paradises of legend.
  footnotes:
    - The 'spring-grass verses' (춘초구) and 'bamboo-branch songs' (죽지사) are traditional poetic and musical forms, suggesting refined literary entertainment.
    - Chukseok Tower is a famous historical pavilion where literati gathered for poetry and contemplation.
